The best investments for a 401k at early 20’s generally involve some level of diversification including: 
• Equities (stocks), which offer the potential for significant long-term growth; 
• Fixed income investments (bonds) that provide income and slightly less risk than equities; 
• Mutual funds and exchange-traded funds (ETFs) that hold a variety of portfolio assets, which make asset allocation easier; 
• Money market instruments (CDs, savings accounts, etc.) that provide a safe haven for principal. 
Since retirement is many years down the road, it’s important to choose investments with the potential for the greatest long-term gains. A mix of equity and fixed income investments, along with some diversification through mutual funds and ETFs, should provide a healthy balance of risk and reward.
